<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="TSJN-01-04-02-pb-0115">[115<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=TSJN/Pages/TSJN-01-04/TSJN-01-04-02-pb-0115.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
<div class="note-source" id="TSJN-01-04-0137-sn"><p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipient's copy ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Library of Virginia, Richmond ]">Vi</span>); in TJs hand. The enclosure, presumably in Linctots hand, has certification signed by Brodhead on face of document (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Library of Virginia, Richmond ]">Vi</span>). Letter and enclosure are endorsed: Fort Pitt July 3rd. 1780 Indian affairs  534.1.3.</p>
<p>On Linctot as Indian agent see Wis. Hist. Soc., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Colls.</span>, <span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">xxiv</span>, 176, note.</p></div>
